From: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Date: Wed, 6 Dec 2017 09:50:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] efi: Move some sysfs files to be read-only by root
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.14.6
Git-commit: af97a77bc01ce49a466f9d4c0125479e2e2230b6

commit af97a77bc01ce49a466f9d4c0125479e2e2230b6 upstream.

Thanks to the scripts/leaking_addresses.pl script, it was found that
some EFI values should not be readable by non-root users.

So make them root-only, and to do that, add a __ATTR_RO_MODE() macro to
make this easier, and use it in other places at the same time.

